# Cohere Code Notes Reference Rule

When working in this repository:

- Read relevant docs in `docs/cohere/code_notes/` before or during code analysis to build context on existing Cohere-specific behavior.
- Treat `docs/cohere/code_notes/upstream-diff.md` as the entry point, then drill into the topic-specific notes it references.
- If you discover new behavior, constraints, pitfalls, or integration details not already documented, update `docs/cohere/code_notes/`.
- New findings may be added to an existing note or captured in a new Markdown file under `docs/cohere/code_notes/`.
- Keep updates concise, behavior-focused, and useful for future maintainers.
